      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "TACOMA, Nov. 10.-In six years\nfrom now, says ]. ]. Hill, head of\nthe Great Northern and Northern\nPacific railroads, the home con-\nsumption of wheat will be so great\nthat none of the cereal will be\nsent across the water.\n\n\nHill and his party were guests\nof the chamber of commerce at a\nbanquet last night. He addressed\nthe gathering on railroad enter\nprises and possibilities, and con-\ntinued his remarks along the lines\nof expectation and importation."
    }
